# First Aid App - Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## Project Overview
**Project Name:** First Aid Emergency Guide App
**Purpose:** College Project - Emergency Medical Response Application
**Target Users:** General public needing quick access to first aid procedures
**Platform:** Android (Minimum SDK 24, Target SDK 34)

## Core Objectives
1. Provide instant access to life-saving first aid procedures
2. Enable offline access to critical emergency information
3. Facilitate quick emergency contact dialing
4. Ensure intuitive, accessible UI for high-stress situations

## Key Features

### Phase 1: Foundation (COMPLETED ✅)
- ✅ Project setup and configuration
- ✅ Database architecture with Room
- ✅ Navigation structure
- ✅ Basic UI layouts

### Phase 2: Core Functionality (COMPLETED ✅)
- ✅ Browse guides by category
- ✅ Search functionality
- ✅ View detailed step-by-step guides
- ✅ Emergency contact management
- ✅ Call emergency services

### Phase 3: Content & Polish (IN PROGRESS)
- ⏳ Expand guide library (currently 4 guides)
- ⏳ Add more emergency contacts
- ⏳ Improve error handling
- ⏳ Add user preferences

### Phase 4: Enhancement (PENDING)
- ❌ Accessibility features
- ❌ Performance optimization
- ❌ Data backup/restore
- ❌ Analytics and usage tracking

### Phase 5: Quality Assurance (PENDING)
- ❌ Unit testing
- ❌ UI testing
- ❌ User acceptance testing

## Success Criteria for College Project
1. ✅ App builds and runs without errors
2. ✅ All core features functional
3. ✅ Professional UI/UX design
4. ⏳ Comprehensive guide content (minimum 10 guides)
5. ⏳ Error-free operation
6. ❌ Test coverage >50%
7. ⏳ Documentation complete

## Technical Stack
- **Language:** Kotlin
- **Architecture:** MVVM with Repository Pattern
- **Database:** Room (SQLite)
- **UI:** Material Design 3, ViewBinding
- **Navigation:** Navigation Component
- **Async:** Kotlin Coroutines + LiveData
- **Dependency Injection:** Manual (can upgrade to Hilt)

## Content Requirements
### Minimum Viable Product (MVP):
- 10+ First Aid Guides covering:
  - CPR (Adult, Child, Infant) ✅
  - Choking ✅
  - Bleeding/Wounds ✅
  - Burns ✅
  - Fractures ⏳
  - Poisoning ⏳
  - Shock ⏳
  - Heart Attack ⏳
  - Stroke ⏳
  - Allergic Reactions ⏳

### Emergency Contacts:
- ✅ 911 Emergency Services
- ✅ Poison Control
- ⏳ Local Hospital
- ⏳ Fire Department
- ⏳ Police (Non-emergency)

## Quality Standards
- All features must work offline
- Response time < 1 second for search
- No crashes or ANRs
- Professional UI following Material Design
- Accessible for screen readers
- Clear, medically accurate content

## Future Enhancements (Post-College)
- Multi-language support
- Video demonstrations
- CPR timer/metronome
- Location-based emergency services
- Share guides via SMS
- Dark mode
